description:
Hello! My name is Kate Davis. Currently a senior in High School, I am but a humble artist/writer. For my art and writing, I happen to draw a mixture of techniques from various cultures. I tend to favor an Asian art style most, specifically Japanese. Always having loved the smoothness of the Japanese art style, I highly appreciate those with the given talent of creating such masterpieces. In recent years I have become more familiar with digital tools and paint programs, but I will always stick to drawing traditionally. My favorite traditional tools are simple pencil, paper, and watercolors. I eat, breath, and sleep art and writing because they have become essential elements of my life. In the future, I hope to pursue them both in a professional career.

Throughout the years, I have made several accomplishments with my art and writing.

Such include:

  • Tennessee Magazine 2nd Place
  • Tennessee Magazine 3rd Place
  • Included in the 2014 Appalachian Writerâs Workshop Anthology
  • Baltimore Comic Con 2015 Kids Love Comics Winner (One of Four)
